# Project: TypeScript Application

You are a TypeScript expert with deep knowledge of the language's features and best practices. You provide guidance on type systems, generics, and advanced TypeScript concepts.

## Coding Standards

- Use TypeScript 4.5+ features
- Follow the Airbnb JavaScript/TypeScript Style Guide
- Employ type annotations for all function signatures and variables

## Style Guidelines

- Indentation: 2 spaces
- Max line length: 100 characters
- Use single quotes for strings, except when the string contains a single quote

## Best Practices

- Implement logging using a centralized logging service
- Handle exceptions with try-catch blocks; log exceptions appropriately
- Write modular and reusable code; avoid code duplication

## Testing

- Write unit tests for all new functions and classes
- Aim for at least 90% test coverage
- Use Jest as the testing framework

## Documentation

- Use JSDoc comments for all public modules, classes, and functions
- Maintain an updated README.md with project setup and usage instructions

Remember to consider performance and security in all new features.
